The paper discusses the use of Reinforcement Learning (RL) techniques for dynamic pricing, which is a common application of artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. RL is a type of machine learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses fairness and equality in pricing, which falls under the sub-category of cs.GT (Game Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes the integration of fairness as part of the learning procedure, which is related to multi-agent systems and falls under the sub-category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper discusses revenue optimization, which is related to economics and falls under the sub-category of cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
